  "git_commit": "not-a-git-repository",
  "known_limitations": [
    "Simplified low-dimensional CPU domains remain the only integrated main-suite result domains; new higher-dimensional domains are prototypes and are not yet main MPC evidence.",
    "Theory covers a stylized one-step separation, finite-threshold split calibration, and sampled-set optimality only.",
    "Citation metadata has source notes, but final publisher-exported BibTeX should be checked before submission.",
    "The max-out 57,000-row matrix was not fully executed in this focused run.",
    "The iclr_submission artifacts are Phase-0 seeds copied from the bounded manuscript, not evidence that the max-out prompt is complete.",
    "The trained dynamics artifacts are diagnostic and integrated only in the separate Stage-A runner, not the original focused-suite runner.",
    "The expanded trained-dynamics Stage-A run covers D0-D5, L0-L3, seeds 0-4, and candidate budget 24; it is not a Stage-B/Stage-C max-out run.",
    "Preliminary learned risk-model validation is diagnostic only and is not yet integrated into held-out planner results.",
    "Calibration label-source ablation is offline from Stage-A logs and does not replace a dedicated executed-rollout calibration split.",
    "The Stage-A executed-rollout calibration split controls held-out step-level violations in this diagnostic but has high accepted plan-failure rates and is not a fresh Stage-B split.",
    "The trained-dynamics Stage-B pilot covers only eight key methods, one candidate budget, one calibration-context budget, and held-out seeds 5-9; it is not the full Stage-B matrix.",
    "The Stage-B pilot again shows mixed results: CCR-MPC improves over vanilla and uncalibrated CCR, but conformal/oracle rows are safer and CVaR/robust rows can be lower cost."
  ],
